item.title: File help
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“halflive9, post:1, topic:401666”]Dear moparscapers,

I have a source with a class inside its called castlewars. But when i open it this came up:

b9hqg8.jpg800×600

Can someone help me? Is there any way to make something from the symbols?[/quote]

You can’t read/change class files directly. (Well I suppose you could, but it wouldn’t help much). If you have the source file, then you should just change that, and not worry about the class files. If you don’t have the source, then I would suggest decompiling the class file. A simple google search for “java class decompiler” should be sufficient.
